**\\n\\nI'm wondering if I could dynamically create a class named something like `oracle.jdbc.nativeimage.Target_oracle_jdbc_proxy_GeneratedProxiesRegistry_Key@<hash>`. The hash is unknown, but I could use identityHashCode after construction. \\n\\nHowever, overriding Object.toString might not be an option. I'm thinking of using the target generatedRegistry.get return value which is null to bypass issues related to wrong class names on line 85. \\n\\nMaybe I could employ a custom ClassLoader to map arbitrary names, allowing Class.forName to succeed. But I’m not entirely sure how binary name validation works when a class is loaded. It’s quite tricky!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Field Access in Reflection**\\n\\nI'm thinking that it probably doesn’t verify, and I don’t need to compile it. If this approach works, then it should cover the getConstructor reference on line 98. \\n\\nI can set the target factory's `classLoader` field to a custom ClassLoader, which the system will use if it's non-null.\\n\\nHowever, I need to ensure that I add the appropriate field access in the reflect-config to make this all work smoothly. It feels a bit involved, but I'm optimistic!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Updating class loading**\\n\\nI'm considering the current setup with the direct prepareProxy passing Service.class and ManualProxy.class, while noting that the classLoader field is non-null. It's good to know that it won't use the superclass classloader. I think I need to set the `classLoader` varhandle here. Since there’s no need to use the previous classloader for the factory instance, I’ll also update the reflection configuration to include a classLoader field that allows writing. I’ll need to make edits for that.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_237XGOALpqvlL6yLsa1vyQI0|fc_05913a7d381ff8d10169f81a9a17a881a082d65985e377e4ac", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.oracle.database.jdbc/ojdbc11/23.8.0.25.04/src/test/java/com_oracle_database_jdbc/ojdbc11/TargetOracleJdbcProxyProxyFactoryTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    private static final String TARGET_REGISTRY_CLASS_NAME =\n            \"oracle.jdbc.nativeimage.Target_oracle_jdbc_proxy_GeneratedProxiesRegistry\";\n", "newText": "    private static final String TARGET_REGISTRY_CLASS_NAME =\n            \"oracle.jdbc.nativeimage.Target_oracle_jdbc_proxy_GeneratedProxiesRegistry\";\n    private static final String TARGET_REGISTRY_KEY_CLASS_NAME =\n            \"oracle.jdbc.nativeimage.Target_oracle_jdbc_proxy_GeneratedProxiesRegistry_Key\";\n"}, {"oldText": "        Object factory = factoryLookup.findConstructor(factoryType, MethodType.methodType(void.class)).invoke();\n        VarHandle generatedRegistry = factoryLookup.findStaticVarHandle(\n                factoryType, \"generatedRegistry\", registryType);\n", "newText": "        Object factory = factoryLookup.findConstructor(factoryType, MethodType.methodType(void.class)).invoke();\n        VarHandle classLoader = factoryLookup.findVarHandle(factoryType, \"classLoader\", ClassLoader.class);\n        classLoader.set(factory, new GeneratedProxyClassLoader());\n        VarHandle generatedRegistry = factoryLookup.findStaticVarHandle(\n                factoryType, \"generatedRegistry\", registryType);\n"}, {"oldText": "    @SuppressWarnings(\"unchecked\")\n    private static Object extractDelegate(Object proxy) {\n        return ProxyFactory.extractDelegate((_Proxy_<Object>) proxy);\n    }\n", "newText": "    @SuppressWarnings(\"unchecked\")\n    private static Object extractDelegate(Object proxy) {\n        return ProxyFactory.extractDelegate((_Proxy_<Object>) proxy);\n    }\n\n    private static final class GeneratedProxyClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        GeneratedProxyClassLoader() {\n            super(TargetOracleJdbcProxyProxyFactoryTest.class.getClassLoader());\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (name.startsWith(TARGET_REGISTRY_KEY_CLASS_NAME + \"@\")) {\n                return Class.forName(generatedProxyClassName(), false, getParent());\n            }\n            return super.loadClass(name, resolve);\n        }\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 843, "output": 1884, "cacheRead": 84480, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 87207, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777867386131, "responseId": "resp_05913a7d381ff8d10169f81a7aec1081a0b57e3d741ff00413"}}
